commit.message:
Strip any junk preceding boost_lib_version

When configuring projects with the NVIDIA HPC SDK's C++ compiler
( https://developer.nvidia.com/hpc-sdk ) I find that the preprocessor
tends to add material from implicitly-included header files before the
main body of even a trivial program, which caused the regexp previously
here to fail to match, which caused a configure using boost.m4 to fail
at:

```
checking for Boost's header version...
configure: error: invalid value: boost_major_version=''
```

commit.message: Restore BOOST_ATOMIC behaviour
Allow clang to fail on travis

Use the correctly numbered variable

By reading the code (and doing some tests) it seemed that
_BOOST_FIND_LIBS used an undocumented seventh parameter. This has now
been documented and the ERROR_ON_UNUSABLE uses have been fixed.
Don't fail in lib searches when headers are not found

Allow not failing for all lib-detections

Also fixes the call to BOOST_FIND_LIB from BOOST_ATOMIC
Allow non-failure on unfound libs
